      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): persist sender metadata in user turn transcript JSONL",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n- Group chat user messages persisted to the session JSONL transcript were missing `__openclaw` sender identity metadata (`senderId`, `senderName`, `senderUsername`) that direct (1:1) session records already carry.\n- Fix: Thread sender identity from the channel inbound context through `UserTurnInput` → `buildUserTurnSenderMeta` into the persisted JSONL `__openclaw` envelope. When no sender metadata is available, the `__openclaw` block is omitted.\n- Scope: Session transcript persistence only. Does not change live turn handling, channel transport, or gateway behavior.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.types.ts`: add `senderId`, `senderName`, `senderUsername` to `UserTurnInput`\n- `src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.ts`: add `buildUserTurnSenderMeta()` and thread `__openclaw` into persisted message\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.ts`: pass `SenderId`/`SenderName`/`SenderUsername` from session context\n- `src/infra/exec-policy.ts`: restore `...baseWithoutMode` spread so mode is not leaked when only security/ask fields are overridden\n- `src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.test.ts`: two new regression tests (sender metadata, empty sender)\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Before (negative control — `git checkout origin/main -- src/sessions/ src/auto-reply/`):**\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx -e \"...\"\nHas __openclaw: false\n__openclaw: null\n```\n\n**After (fix applied):**\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx -e \"...\"\nHas __openclaw: true\n__openclaw: {\"senderId\":\"8489979671\",\"senderName\":\"Ram Shenoy\",\"senderUsername\":\"ram_s\"}\nNo-sender has __openclaw: false\n```\n\n**Vitest:**\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.test.ts --run\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  29 passed (29)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/exec-policy.test.ts --run\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  2 passed (2)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/90531-group-session-sender-metadata",
